1999-01-18  kulow  <kulow@xanadu>

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc: fixes

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in: Hmm, I'm not guilty,
    but libtool refuses to link libpykde.la:

    libtool: link: error: cannot link shared libraries into libtool
    libraries

    I'm not sure why - it never had been there before. I have not really
    an idea why. ;( I guess, I will have to try a newer release when
    anoncvs.gnu.org comes back.

    Torben: please try to find out, which library you exactly need to
    dlopen the library. libtool says, that you have to link against all
    libraries that the dloped module depends on, but this is of course
    a bit optimistic ;(

    If nothing helps, we simply patch libtool. The code exists, because
    it doesn't know how to handle libkom.la, since it doesn't know if
    libkom will be installed when you use a wrapper in the sources... (if
    you got that explanation ;)

