1999-01-16  kulow  <kulow@xanadu>

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc: better handling of the
    regenerating rule. Cd into $top_srcdir before relying on $0

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc: CVS_SILENT next try

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in: CVS_SILENT: I hope
    noone noticed ;)

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc: fixing automoc to support
    lib*_la_METASOURCES

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc: small fixes

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc,
    /home/kde/kde-common/admin/ChangeLog: wow - call me Perl expert now
    ;-) [I love learning by problemshaving]

    automoc supports now Makefile.ins that want their moc files included.
    It will look for .moc files listed in METASOURCES. For those it
    looks for the corrosponding .h file (just by replacing the suffix!)
    And it looks for a *.cc|*.cpp|*.cxx|*.C file that includes the moc
    file. For both the header and source file it generates the correct
    build rule. I would like to have support for checking if the MOC
    files are in DISTCLEAN, but that's too complex for me ;)

    To prevent automoc to run over one file twice, it supports a
    comment DO_NOT_USE_AUTOMOC which it adds it itself and looks for
    while parsing.  An interesting methode for Torben to keep it away ;-)

    To be honest: 99% of the MOC rules in CVS's Makefiles are wrong
    for builddir != src and the remaining 1% are Makefiles that use
    AUTOMOC.  Since I agree with Torben that using moc_*.cpp files
    increases compilation time I had to find a way to generate the
    rules automaticly.

    Greetings, Stephan (wishing to have a book ;)

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in,
    /home/kde/kde-common/admin/ChangeLog: support builddir != src also
    in the modules, that support dynamic subdirs

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/automoc,
    /home/kde/kde-common/admin/ChangeLog: Having no idea about perl,
    I played hard to get this running ;)

    Better command line parsing (now, --version and -verbose|-v is
    supported).

    automoc looks now for METASOURCES and if it's found it looks in
    them for USE_AUTOMOC. If this tag is found, it works like before,
    if not it will try to be clever and fill the Makefile with all kind
    of support for .moc files. But for this I need some more Perl magic,
    so it may take a while ;)

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in,
    /home/kde/kde-common/admin/ChangeLog: added aliases for libkio
    and libkdeutil

