1998-12-23  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/optionsdlg.h: changed options dialog to NOT be modal. Yay.

    * src/kagenda.cpp: fixed a bug where even if 24 hour time was
    selected, the timesheet was showing incorrect (12 hour) values.

    * src/kmonthview.cpp, src/kagenda.cpp: CVS_SILENT more stupid fixes.
    That'll teach me to commit w/o compiling...

    * src/kpropradio.h: CVS_SILENT removed function prototype, whoops.

    * src/ktimed.cpp, src/kpropradio.cpp, src/kmonthview.cpp,
    src/kagenda.cpp, src/calprinter.cpp, src/baselistview.cpp: fixed
    up 12/24 hour time format, it was still broken. also removed the
    setState(const char *) stuff from kpropradio, it was broken and
    silly. :)

    * src/optionsdlg.cpp: disabled date format stuff in options, because
    it doesn't work yet.

    * src/kpropradio.h, src/kpropradio.cpp, src/kagenda.cpp: made
    kpropradios able to understand boolean config values.

    * src/ktimed.cpp, src/kmonthview.cpp, src/kagenda.cpp,
    src/baselistview.cpp: made all the default values for "Time Format
    (24 hr or am/pm)" the same.

    * src/topwidget.cpp: if autosave is on, and the calendar needs to
    save and it has no name, it will generate one.

    * src/topwidget.cpp: added hinting icons next to cut/copy/paste in
    edit menu.

    * src/optionsdlg.cpp, src/kagenda.cpp: default color to fall back
    on in kagenda for the sheet background.

    * src/optionsdlg.cpp, src/kpropradio.h, src/kpropradio.cpp: more
    fixups to options.  Made KPropRadio::addRadio return a pointer to
    the radio button so it can be manipulated further.

    * src/topwidget.cpp: fixed default appointment time setting.

    * src/topwidget.cpp, src/main.cpp, src/kpropspin.cpp: re-patched
    kpropspin to strip off suffixes, which vespa somehow destroyed during
    conflict resolution?!? A few other minor fixups.

    * src/topwidget.h, src/topwidget.cpp, src/aboutdlg.cpp: made
    contributers' names more prominent in the about dialog.  Fixed "New
    Window" option so it opens a blank calendar, not a duplicate of the
    one you are editing (which causes massive problems).

    * src/topwidget.cpp: fixed View-->Day entry in the menu.  It was
    cycling through the various views, not selecting single day view.
    The correct code was commented out?  and replaced with something else;
    must have been an experiment that we forgot to reverse.

