1998-09-03  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/todoview.cpp: removed some debug code.

    * src/todoview.cpp, src/kdpevent.cpp, src/editeventwin.cpp,
    src/calobject.cpp, src/TODO, src/BUGS: whoops.  Accidentally
    introduced a recursive call in calobject. Fixed.  Other very minor
    updates.

    * src/kmonthview.cpp: multi-day appointments are now handled pretty
    sanely by month view.

    * src/topwidget.h, src/topwidget.cpp, src/ksellabel.h,
    src/ksellabel.cpp, src/kmonthview.h, src/kmonthview.cpp, src/BUGS:
    double clicking on date headers in month view creates a new no-time
    event.

    * src/ktimed.cpp, src/editeventwin.cpp, src/BUGS: time editor works
    with 24 hour mode preference.

    * src/ktimed.cpp, src/kagenda.cpp, src/eventwidget.cpp, src/BUGS:
    almost fixed problem when dragging events to the end of the agenda
    view.  It sets start time to 11:00 PM, but end time to 00:00 AM (the
    next day).  This is kind of bad, I don't really know how to deal
    with it yet for it not to seem like the event actually spans two days.

    Also modified ktimed so that it takes up arrow to subtract 15 minutes,
    and down arrow to add 15 minutes.  You can type your own time, too.

1998-09-02  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/versit/vobject.c: fixed problem with quoted-printable strings
    not having '=' written out correctly (it had to be escaped).

    * src/topwidget.cpp, src/alarmmain.cpp: damnit one last fix to
    process id stuff.

    * src/calobject.cpp, src/alarmmain.cpp: fixed a problem with a
    pointer being used before initialization.  Was causing alarmd to
    crash on my system, but not korganizer.  weird shit.

    * src/version.h, src/topwidget.cpp, src/printdialog.cpp,
    src/optionsdlg.cpp, src/calobject.cpp, src/TODO, src/BUGS: hopefully
    time zone stuff is really working more or less now.  Actually, I'm
    not sure what "correct" behaviour should be when the time zone in
    a vCalendar conflicts with what the user has configured.  I need to
    discuss this on KDE devel.  Right now the time zone in the kconfig
    file just acts as a "Default" time zone if none is already specified.

    * src/topwidget.cpp, src/main.cpp, src/calobject.cpp, src/BUGS:
    fixed handling of session management.  Fixes to traversal code for
    prev/next, should work even with recurring events now.

