1998-07-27  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/doc/en/Makefile.am, src/topwidget.h, src/topwidget.cpp,
    src/kagenda.cpp, src/calobject.h, src/calobject.cpp, src/TODO:
    cut/copy/paste routines moved to CalObject from topwidget.  Not really
    tested. Added a ln -s korganizer.html index.html for the documentation
    in the makefile.  Updates to TODO list.

    * README: updates for 0.9.9

    * src/pixmaps/send.xpm, src/pixmaps/Makefile.am, src/main.cpp,
    src/kptbutton.cpp, src/kdpevent.cpp, src/editeventwin.cpp,
    src/calobject.cpp, src/TODO, src/BUGS: bug fixes for the alarm daemon.
    Now recognizes a stale lockfile, removes it, and restarts the daemon
    whenever korganizer is started.  Other minor cleanups.

    * src/topwidget.cpp, src/kagenda.h, src/kagenda.cpp,
    src/eventwidget.cpp, src/TODO: bugfixes and cleanups for dragging and
    resizing.  The one major bug that remains that I know about is how
    screwed up things get if you drag a recurring event to a new date.
    We need to implement the copy constructor for KDPEvents and then
    make an exception to the recurring event, copy it, and then insert
    this new event as the exception to the rule.

