1998-05-12  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/versit/vobject.h, src/versit/vcc.y, src/versit/vcc.c,
    src/versit/Makefile.am, src/topwidget.h, src/topwidget.cpp,
    src/todoview.h, src/todoview.cpp, src/searchdialog.h,
    src/searchdialog.cpp, src/kdpevent.h, src/kdpevent.cpp,
    src/eventwindetails.h, src/eventwindetails.cpp, src/editeventwin.cpp,
    src/calobject.cpp, src/baselistview.cpp: Oh my god, where to start?
    Some final fixups for searching, I'm going to leave it alone for
    awhile.  It isn't that pretty but, it is at least mostly functional.
    I also fixed a bug for multi-day appointments where they were getting
    written to the save file for each day they happened on.  This caused
    the saved calendar to balloon each time it was loaded and saved.
    Not good -- manually check your calendar to see if you have repeated
    events, and if so, remove the extra occurrences.

    Started adding due date support to todo list, but stopped when I
    got side-tracked.

    Mainly, I worked hard on starting to get attendees / group
    scheduling started.  It was a good effort and the ball is rolling.
    Attendee stuff is saved across a load and a save, and that part of
    the "details" dialog is implemented, if not "perfectly."  I am going
    to keep going on this stuff for awhile. Hopefully others can handle
    bugs while I work on this feature.

