1998-04-06  kulow  <kulow@xanadu>

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in: split the KDE paths
    check into three: kde headers, kde libraries, kde paths.  This takes
    a little longer, but all those "configure can't run a little KDE
    program. Do I have to install kdelibs before kdeadmin?" mails go out
    of my mailbox. Why to people think, the correct installation order
    is ABC? ;-)

    * /home/kde/kde-common/admin/acinclude.m4.in: added a bigger check
    for -lsocket and co

