1998-02-18  Preston Brown  <pbrown@xanadu>

    * src/kagenda.h, src/optionsdlg.cpp, src/optionsdlg.h,
    src/topwidget.cpp, src/topwidget.h, src/kagenda.cpp, src/BUGS:
    fuck yeah.  options dialog is doing things. :)  Only one thing is
    hooked up right now, and that is 12 hr / 24 hour time.  But at least
    fester will be happy.

    architecture goes like this:  when topwidget sees the optionsdlg
    close(), it emits configChanged(), which is connected to agendaView
    (the only one receiving it, right now) in the slot updateConfig().
    agendaView then can read anything it wants (in this case, the time
    value) and process it.  It works like a charm.

